This paper discusses the tension between openness and prudence in AI research, which is a core issue in the field of AI. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI. The paper also discusses potential harms arising from misuse of research, which could fall under the categories of cs.CY (cybersecurity) and cs.CR (cryptography and security). Additionally, the paper explores implications for responsible publication norms in AI research, which could relate to cs.RO (robotics) and cs.LG (machine learning).
